title: CityCorner-SarahT-YuppyPuppies-September2025_STLTV
comments: Host/producer Sarah Thompson speaks with Jessica Cooke, founder of Yuppy Puppies Forever Pet Rescue. The St. Louis-area business owner and pet advocate saw a heartbreaking need — pets left behind when their owners passed away — and started Yuppy Puppies Forever. The nonprofit is dedicated to giving orphaned pets a second chance at love and family. Jessica shares the organization’s mission, work and how they’re meeting a growing need to give pets hope and new beginnings. Learn more at https://yuppypuppyspa.com/yp-rescues
cgTitle: City Corner - Yuppy Puppies Forever Pet Rescue

title: CityCorner-SarahB-UnitedWayPartners-September2025_STLTV
comments: Host Sarah Bernard chats with Michelle Tucker, ceo of United Way about three organizations that benefit from the United Way's campaign: Catholic Charities, St. Louis Area Foodbank and The Red Cross.
cgTitle: City Corner -United Way's Impact

title: CityCorner-Todd-PowderValley-WildeyTheatre-September2025_STLTV
comments: Host Todd Blackstock discusses the Powder Valley Nature Conservation Center with Manager Scoot Sarantakis and Naturalist Matthew Cavanaugh. Also, Blackstock chats with Al Canal, former comedian and entertainment director of The Wildey Theatre in Edwardsville about the history and renovation of the historic architecture and a few upcoming shows
cgTitle: Powder Valley Nature Center & Wildey Theatre
